    <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm mb-4">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="h4 mb-3">3. External data sources in this project</h2>
        <p class="mb-2">Fetching data from APIs keeps content fresher and reduces manual copy-paste maintenance. One source can feed multiple pages with consistent, up-to-date information.</p>
        <p class="mb-2">On-site usage examples include tables, content cards, homepage highlights, metric counters, and filterable lists built from the same source data.</p>
        <ul class="mb-0">
          <li>Research.fi (publications)</li>
          <li>Canva Connect API (presentations)</li>
          <li>YouTube Data API v3 (playlists/videos)</li>
          <li>GitHub API (site changes table)</li>
          <li>OuluREPO (theses)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="h4 mb-3">4. Popular-level roadmap to build your own site</h2>
        <ol class="mb-0">
          <li>Bring AI in from step one: ask for a plan first, then implement in small, reviewable change batches.</li>
          <li>Create a GitHub repository and pick a simple stack (Eleventy + Bootstrap works well).</li>
          <li>Start small: one base template and a few pages.</li>
          <li>Add multilingual support only after your core structure works.</li>
          <li>Integrate one API at a time and keep a cache fallback.</li>
          <li>Automate build and deploy with CI/CD.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
